rComments: His examples are quite clear, his lectures short and concise. He is a though grader but he lets you know what is expected from him from the beginning, if he says 30 points if you mess this, you will loose 30 points don't doubt it.

He starts class 15 minutes later, and ends it pretty early too. He tries to make jokes by talking about his wife. I went in for office hours, and he helps but I can tell that he really dislikes doing it.

When you take your time and pay attention to one of his examples, you are going to get the concept and fully understand it. He tells you what he expects of you in the first day and he is not going to change his mind. His tests are difficult but not unexpected and he grades fairly. The lab reports are perhaps the thing you have to work in the most
He is a good prof generally
